The living room opens out to a manicured garden setting that brings the natural elements indoors. It features a comfy, new couch that folds out to house additional guests. The kitchen is fully stocked, and allows you to make a perfect meal that you can enjoy al fresco. For those looking to stay in and relax, complimentary cable is provided on the Smart TV in the living room.The bedroom features a plush king-size bed, with soothing sheets that will give you that perfect night's sleep. The bathroom is completely updated, with a shower/tub combination that serves as the ideal place to relax and unwind. There is something very special and welcoming about this quiet and picturesque gated community. From the splendid mountain views to the meticulously maintained grounds, we offer you the luxury and convenience of a resort, with the comfort and conveniences of a condo that will make you feel like you're home.Guest accessYou’re renting the entire condo and outdoor area. Make yourself at home, as everything is yours to enjoy exclusively!Other things to noteCITY OF PALM SPRINGS REGULATIONS & RENTAL RULES(we don't make the rules, but we do follow them!)**No parties or large social gatherings of any kind are permitted at this location!** Neighbors have been notified that this property is a vacation rental and are encouraged to call a hotline to dispatch authorities to investigate any disturbances. If the city issues a violation, guest will be responsible for payment of any fine(s) and may be evicted with no refund.- Minimum age for primary renting guest is 25.- Daytime max occupancy is 6 people.- Overnight max occupancy is 4 people (2 in bedroom, 2 on couch).- Maximum of 2 vehicles allowed.- The City imposes a strict noise ordinance for vacation rentals. No music is allowed outside at any time, including music coming from inside that can be heard at the property line, and no noise at all is allowed outside after 10pm.- The City requires a signed written contract for all guests, as well as a copy of the primary renter's government ID. This will be taken care of during check-in.ARRIVAL/DEPARTURE- Check-in time is 4PM, and check-out is promptly by 11AM.- Our onsite greeter will meet you at the home and give you a tour.- Keycard for the community gate is provided. If keycard is lost, guest will have an additional fee of $150 to replace it.- Late check-outs without prior approval with incur a $250 fee, as we need time to get the house ready for the next guest.PETS- Pets are allowed (1 pet max, under 25 lbs), with a fee of $250 per month. Pets must be approved and fee paid prior to check-in. Any signs of pets on the property without our knowledge will incur an additional $500 fee and will be cause for eviction.NO SMOKING- There is no smoking in the unit or any of the common areas of the complex. Any signs of smoking in the unit will incur an additional $250 fee.CLEANINGFinal cleaning after your checkout is included in your reservation quote. For stays longer than 6 weeks, guest will be responsible for the cost of a mid-stay clean every 30 days. Funds for mid-stay cleanings will be collected from guest as they occur.ELECTRICITY SURCHARGE (JUNE-SEPT A/C)-Guests are responsible for electric bill during the summer months. Expense is not included in the reservation. We require a $500/mo deposit in advance of your stay. After checkout, if electric bill is lower than the $500 deposit amount, the difference will be refunded to you. We recommend never setting the AC below 73°, as any lower could cause the system to freeze over and stop working,We want to ensure you’ll love your stay in Palm Springs. Please let us know if you have any questions. We’re happy to help.

property_address: Room in Mountain View, California, United States
listing_description: Enjoy easy access to everything from this perfectly located home base. Walk to Castro Street. Enjoy everything Mountain View has to offer. With this listing you are renting a private bedroom in a larger communal home. Shared kitchen, bathroom, living room and laundry. Close to Silicon Valley giants. Expect to share the home with young techies and interns. That being said...we have pretty strict House Rules. We do this for the safety and comfort of everyone. Be prepared to be respectful.The spaceYou are renting a private bedroom in a 4 bedroom home. The bed in this room is a king size bed. There is one bathroom in the hallway for your use. For this reason we have added sinks to two of the bedrooms, so alleviate bathroom traffic.We’ve taken great effort to create a comfortable, convenient home for people visiting the area. The common shared space is a living room with a seating area for conversation and tv viewing and a large table for workig. MONTH TO MONTH We can accept a longer booking, but we would do it on a month to month basis.You can book 31 days now. This will give you the benefit of a monthly discount and you would avoid the city short term rental tax.You won't pay additional Airbnb fees since the fees are based on a percentage. You will pay an additional cleaning fee. We will come in monthly and clean your room and look for maintenance issues at that time.This is a home share situation and there are more stringent House Rules (in the listing) that we all need to follow for peaceful living. The majority of guests in this home are staying for several months at a time.When you book thru Airbnb, you are booking a short term rental. Your stay is not a tenancy. Keeping stays at 31 days helps establish your stay as a short term stay not a tenancy.MAIL Because this is a short term rental, not a tenancy, you cannot use the house address to receive mail. There are local stores where you can rent mail boxes or receive packages. Often they are inside grocery stores.COVID CHANGES We offer anti-bacterial gel and disinfectant at the entrance and encourage use. We ask that no outside shoes be worn in the home, unless they have been disinfected on the bottom. We ask all guests to disinfect the bathroom sink area and toilet after they use it. We provide supplies.RESPECT is a huge theme and focus for us. You will be staying with people from various countries with various cultural backgrounds and habits. We ask that you try to keep this in mind. Please be considerate beyond what you might normally be. You never know if something you are doing may be offensive to someone from a different background. Take personal responsibility to clean after yourself and leave a tidy bathroom and kitchen for the next guest.LOCATION: Just two short blocks from downtown Mountain View Castro Street.VISITORS: This is our Zero Tolerance House Rule. The only people allowed in the home at any time are officially registered guests who have been ID verified. This is for the safety, security and comfort of everyone in the house. You can be assured that your housemate doesn't have a random unknown person in their room and that the house isn't completely overcrowded. If you break this rule Airbnb policy allows for us to cancel your booking without refund.This is not a party house. Your housemates are serious young people who often need to work in the morning. That being said....if you are a several month guest and have a family member or friend accompanying you or visiting you for a a few days, talk to us for permission and guidelines.SECURITY CAMERA: According to Airbnb policy, we want to disclose that we have a Ring Doorbell camera at the front door. It has sound. It will be turned on during your stay. It is a clearly visible camera outside the home. This is for everyone's comfort and protection. We don't have problems in the house, because we take efforts to keep the house safe for you and your things. KITCHEN USE: Using the kitchen is a privilege that is granted to you, if you use it with respect for the others. You can prepare simple meals. No frying fish or cooking with strong spices that leave a lingering odor--what smells good to you may be offensive to others. You are expected to clean up your mess. We do not have cleaning fairies. You must commit to washing your dishes right after use. This means no leaving dishes to soak because you've burned something. If you violate this rule, you may lose kitchen privileges.CLEANING: The cleaning fee that you pay when booking is for preparing the room before your stay and restoring it after you leave. We DO NOT have a daily cleaning service. We have a cleaning person who comes in sometimes. This person maintains the cleanliness of the common area, including the bathrooms, living room and kitchen, but you are expected to clean after yourself. If you would like an additional cleaning, we can arrange it for $40.LAUNDRY: Free on site washer and dryer. You provide your own detergent.CHECKING IN: The house has a coded lock. Each guest will have a different code that is only active while they are staying in the home. Bedrooms have keys. Please don't lose your key. There will be a $100 fee if we need to help you enter the room. The fee can go up to $200 if it is after 10pm.PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION: The house is literally a 3 minute walk to a VTA city bus stop. 5 min walk to Cal Train. 1 hr, 15 min Cal Train ride to San Francisco. You can expect to find shuttle stops of the huge Silicon Valley companies all around the area. Many are at the CalTrain station.Lyft and Uber are quick, easy and inexpensive. PARKING: There is a parking spot in front of the garage. It is not assigned to any particular person. Otherwise you can park on the street.BIKES: Absolutely no bikes in the house or garage. There is plenty of space on the side yard to store bikes.Before you book the wrong place, just know that for things to run smoothly in this type of shared home, we need to run a tight ship. We have rules that we will enforce, so don’t be surprised if we call you out on some violation. We expect a certain standard of behavior from everyone, though we cannot guarantee that everyone will follow the standard we have set. Our only recourse is to cancel the booking of people who violate the house policies. If you feel someone is being disrespectful, you must let us know immediately. We want the opportunity to talk to the other guest and not find out about offensive behavior after your stay has ended.Guest accessYou are renting a private room and you get access to shared space in the home. You can use the living room, dining room, kitchen, laundry, backyard etc. We ask that you respect that it is a shared space.Suggestions:~wipe down all cabinet knobs, refrigerator etc with disinfecting spray and a rag~wear only inside shoes in the house unless you have disinfected them--you can leave all outside shoes near the entry~disinfect the bathroom sink area and toilet after useDuring your stayOur team are all pretty extroverted and social. Feel free to contact us with anything that makes you uncomfortable in the home. We will try to address it immediately. We love order in the home and will be firm with those who completely disregard the House Rules and disrespect fellow guests.Other things to note~~No visitors at all unless I have OKd it and received a link to their ID Verified Airbnb account or a photo ID and extra guest fee.~~No mail service at the home~~We respectfully request no shoes in the home unless they have been disinfected~~You should disinfect the bathroom after you use it~~Extra cleanings can be booked for $40 per hour

I most commonly host interns from G00gle, Mercedes, Tesla and various small start ups.VISITORS: This is our Zero Tolerance House Rule. The only people allowed in the home at any time are officially registered guests who have been ID verified. This is for the safety, security and comfort of everyone in the house. You can be assured that your housemate doesn't have a random unknown person in their room and that the house isn't completely overcrowded. If you break this rule Airbnb policy allows for us to cancel your booking without refund.This is not a party house. Your housemates are serious young people who often need to work in the morning. That being said....if you are a several month guest and have a family member or friend accompanying you or visiting you for a a few days, talk to us for permission and guidelines.SECURITY CAMERA: According to Airbnb policy, we want to disclose that we have a Ring Doorbell camera at the front door. It has sound. It will be turned on during your stay. It is a clearly visible camera outside the home. This is for everyone's comfort and protection. We don't have problems in the house, because we take efforts to keep the house safe for you and your things. KITCHEN USE: Using the kitchen is a privilege that is granted to you, if you use it with respect for the others. You can prepare simple meals. No frying fish or cooking with strong spices that leave a lingering odor--what smells good to you may be offensive to others. You are expected to clean up your mess. We do not have cleaning fairies. You must commit to washing your dishes right after use. This means no leaving dishes to soak because you've burned something. If you violate this rule, you may lose kitchen privileges.CLEANING: The cleaning fee that you pay when booking is for preparing the room before your stay and restoring it after you leave. If you would like an additional cleaning, we can arrange it for $40.LAUNDRY: Free on site washer and dryer. You provide your own detergent. Each guest gets their personal code that works for the front door and their bedroom door.
